content: That's really helpful, thanks for the tips! I'll definitely consider planting some of those flowers in my yard. I've also been reading about how hummingbirds need to eat constantly to fuel their high metabolism, so I can see why they'd be attracted to nectar-rich flowers. By the way, I've been noticing the birds in my backyard a lot more since I set up that new feeder, and I've even started to recognize some of their songs. Speaking of bird songs, I've been trying to identify the birds I hear singing in the morning - do you know of any resources that can help me with that?
